{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"The default value for `clearAlpha` is now `1` which is consistent with the previous behavior of `setClearColor`.","created_at":"2017-10-31T23:24:17.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/12552#issuecomment-340936174","id":340936174,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12552","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0MDkzNjE3NA==","updated_at":"2017-10-31T23:24:26.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/340936174","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/297678?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/trusktr","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI5NzY3OA==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"trusktr","type":"User","id":297678,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"> Changing the default clearAlphato 1 will cause a lot of breakage. \r\n\r\nThat doesn't seem to be a problem, based on Three's release history (and considering it doesn't use SemVer). In this regard, why not just make the defaults the most intuitive? The tests don't indicate any breakage; we could add a test for it, and while we're at it, the test could use the new default value.","created_at":"2017-11-01T00:32:54.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/12552#issuecomment-340945796","id":340945796,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12552","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0MDk0NTc5Ng==","updated_at":"2017-11-01T00:36:38.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/340945796","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/297678?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/trusktr","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI5NzY3OA==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"trusktr","type":"User","id":297678,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"[This is why](https:\/\/stackoverflow.com\/questions\/20495302\/transparent-background-with-three-js\/20496296#20496296) changing the default alpha to 1 will cause breakage.\r\n\r\nI think my suggested fix addresses your concern in a reasonable way.","created_at":"2017-11-01T00:58:41.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/12552#issuecomment-340948896","id":340948896,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12552","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0MDk0ODg5Ng==","updated_at":"2017-11-01T00:58:41.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/340948896","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"I can live with the current API, but it could be cleaner:\r\n\r\nFor example, here's what I have to do currently, when writing a custom element that maps two attributes to clear color and clear alpha:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconstructor() {\r\n    super()\r\n\r\n    \/\/ ...\r\n\r\n    \/\/ default initial color and alpha\r\n    this._glBackgroundOpacity = 1\r\n    this.renderer.setClearColor( new Color(...), this._glBackgroundOpacity )\r\n}\r\n\r\nattributeChangedCallback( attr, oldVal, newVal ) {\r\n\r\n    if ( attr == 'backgroundColor' ) {\r\n        this.renderer.setClearColor( this.processColorValue( newVal ), this._glBackgroundOpacity )\r\n    }\r\n    else if ( attr == 'backgroundOpacity' ) {\r\n        this._glBackgroundOpacity = this.processOpacityValue( newVal )\r\n        this.renderer.setClearAlpha( this._glBackgroundOpacity )\r\n    }\r\n\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nHere's what I'd have to do if we remove `setClearAlpha`:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconstructor() {\r\n    super()\r\n\r\n    \/\/ ...\r\n\r\n    \/\/ default initial color and alpha\r\n    this._glBackgroundColor = new Color(...)\r\n    this._glBackgroundOpacity = 1\r\n    this.renderer.setClearColor( this._glBackgroundColor, this._glBackgroundOpacity )\r\n}\r\n\r\nattributeChangedCallback( attr, oldVal, newVal ) {\r\n\r\n    if ( attr == 'backgroundColor' ) {\r\n        this._glBackgroundColor = this.processColorValue( newVal )\r\n        this.renderer.setClearColor( this._glBackgroundColor, this._glBackgroundOpacity )\r\n    }\r\n    else if ( attr == 'backgroundOpacity' ) {\r\n        this._glBackgroundOpacity = this.processOpacityValue( newVal )\r\n        this.renderer.setClearColor( this._glBackgroundColor, this._glBackgroundOpacity )\r\n    }\r\n    else if ( attr == '...' ) { ... }\r\n\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nFinally, the changes of this PR would prevent people from having to create extra state in cases similar to mine, and that would look like this:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconstructor() {\r\n    super()\r\n\r\n    \/\/ ...\r\n\r\n    \/\/ default initial color and alpha\r\n    this.renderer.setClearColor( new Color(...), 1 )\r\n}\r\n\r\nattributeChangedCallback( attr, oldVal, newVal ) {\r\n\r\n    if ( attr == 'backgroundColor' ) {\r\n        this.renderer.setClearColor( this.processColorValue( newVal ) )\r\n    }\r\n    else if ( attr == 'backgroundOpacity' ) {\r\n        this.renderer.setClearAlpha( this.processOpacityValue( newVal ) )\r\n    }\r\n\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nNo state needed in the last example because the state is in the API. That is the cleanest!","created_at":"2017-11-01T23:24:16.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/12552#issuecomment-341272746","id":341272746,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12552","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0MTI3Mjc0Ng==","updated_at":"2017-11-03T18:08:04.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/341272746","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/297678?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/trusktr","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI5NzY3OA==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"trusktr","type":"User","id":297678,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"> This is why changing the default alpha to 1 will cause breakage.\r\n\r\nYou'll also notice at the bottom of that example it says\r\n\r\n> three.js r.71\r\n\r\nbecause people are all too familiar with breaking releases of Three, so they have gotten accustomed to putting the release version in their StackOverflow answers. It's okay for Three.js releases to have breaking changes, people expect this from Three.js.","created_at":"2017-11-03T18:05:33.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/12552#issuecomment-341783035","id":341783035,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12552","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0MTc4MzAzNQ==","updated_at":"2017-11-03T18:09:53.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/341783035","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/297678?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/trusktr","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI5NzY3OA==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"trusktr","type":"User","id":297678,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"> It's okay for Three.js releases to have breaking changes, people expect this from Three.js.\r\n\r\nThat doesn't mean we should keep breaking things \ud83d\ude1b","created_at":"2017-11-22T10:24:26.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/12552#issuecomment-346307842","id":346307842,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12552","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0NjMwNzg0Mg==","updated_at":"2017-11-22T10:24:26.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/346307842","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":6,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"Closing this for now.","created_at":"2017-11-22T10:24:50.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/12552#issuecomment-346307937","id":346307937,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12552","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0NjMwNzkzNw==","updated_at":"2017-11-22T10:24:50.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/346307937","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":7,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"> That doesn't mean we should keep breaking things \ud83d\ude1b\r\n\r\nHaha, I agree. Using SemVer would be great too! `r1.2.3`, `r2.0.1`, etc, with `r`. \ud83d\ude1c\r\n\r\nThe benefit would be: a patch bump means \"I probably don't have to check release notes unless some bug I was having may have been fixed\". A minor bump means \"hey, I can optionally check the release notes to learn of new features, cool\", and finally a major bump means \"I _must_ check release notes for breaking changes\". It's convenient for other reasons too, f.e. it helps tooling install proper versions while not breaking apps (hopefully).\r\n","created_at":"2017-11-22T19:51:35.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/12552#issuecomment-346456510","id":346456510,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12552","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0NjQ1NjUxMA==","updated_at":"2017-11-22T19:54:15.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/346456510","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/297678?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/trusktr","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI5NzY3OA==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/truskt